 More than 600 people are part of the Havasupai tribe , which is the smallest Indian nation in America .
Visitors can reach the mysterious tribe on foot or by helicopter or mule , and experience life in the village of Supai , which has a cafe , general stores , a lodge , post office and school .
The Indian village was Supai is concealed at the bottom of Havasu Canyon from the National Park rangers in 1975 .